{
  "doc_id": "37257",
  "text": "Sea urchin sperm were obtained from Arbacia punctulata. Animals were purchased from either Duke University Marine Laboratory (J.M.: Keller, Beaufort, NC, USA) or from the Marine Biological Laboratory (MBL) Woods Hole (Woods Hole, MA, USA). Spawning was induced by the injection of 500 μl of 0.5 M KCl into the body cavity [CITATION_1] or by mild electrical stimulation. The released sperm were densely packed, the so-called 'dry' sperm, and was stored on ice during transportation. Before use, sperm were diluted in artificial sea water (432 mM Nacl, 9 mM KCl, 9.27 mM CaCl 2 , 22.94 mM MgCl 2 ; 25.5 mM MgSO 4 ; 0,1 mM EDTA and 10 mM Hepes, pH 7.8) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
